-- BHP Billiton, SacOil Holdings Stock May Move in Early Johannesburg Trading
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-25T06:02:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/bhp-billiton-sacoil-holdings-stock-may-move-in-early-johannesburg-trading.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  dropped for
a third day, sliding 204.26, or 0.7 percent, to 27,413.65 in
Johannesburg.  
 BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ): Lead, nickel, zinc, copper and
aluminum prices fell on the London Metals Exchange. BHP, the
world’s largest mining company, retreated 21 cents, or 0.1
percent, to 219 rand.  
 SacOil Holding Ltd.  (SCL SJ): The petroleum company was
awarded the right to explore an area of Lake Albert in
Democratic Republic of Congo, according to a Presidential decree
published in Congo’s Journal Officiel June 22. SacOil was
unchanged at 18 cents.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 3.8 percent to $18.95
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) declined 0.2 percent to $43.87.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) slid 2.8 percent to $57.31. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) lost 0.7 percent to $4.61. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) fell 0.6 percent to $13.47. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
rose 0.2 percent to $10.26. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US)
dropped 3.7 percent to $24.25. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) slipped 0.5
percent to $3.94. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) declined 3.6 percent to
$36.71.  
